15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Health – General
18 15–101.
19 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
20 (k) “Special pediatric hospital” means a facility in the State that provides
21 nonacute medical, rehabilitation, therapy, and palliative services to individuals:
22 (1) Under the age of 22 years; or
23 (2) Who are at least 2 years old and under the age of 23 years and have
24 co–occurring physical and behavioral health conditions.
25 15–102.3.
26 (m) Beginning January 1, 2026, the provisions of § 15–861 of the Insurance Article
27 apply to managed care organizations in the same manner that they apply to carriers.
28 [(n)] (M) Beginning January 1, 2026, the provisions of § 15–862 of the Insurance
29 Article apply to managed care organizations in the same manner that they apply to carriers.
30 [(o)] (N) The provisions of § 15–863 of the Insurance Article apply to managed
31 care organizations in the same manner they apply to carriers.
32 15–103.

HOUSE BILL 1376 3
1 (a) (1) The Secretary shall administer the Maryland Medical Assistance
2 Program.
3 (2) The Program:
4 (xxvi) Beginning on January 1, 2026, shall provide coverage for a
5 transfer to a special pediatric hospital in accordance with § 15–861 of the Insurance Article
6 § 15–158 OF THIS SUBTITLE;
7 15–158.
8 (A) (1) [The] SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE
9 Program and the Maryland Children’s Health Program may not require prior authorization
10 for a transfer to a special pediatric hospital.
11 (2) AT THE REQUEST OF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL, THE
12 PROGRAM AND THE MARYLAND CHILDREN’S HEALTH PROGRAM SHALL PROVIDE A
13 PRIOR AUTHORIZATION DETERMINATION REGARDING A TRANSFER TO A SPECIAL
14 PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL WITHIN 2 BUSINESS DAYS AFTER THE REQUEST IS RECEIVED.
15 (B) (1) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31, 2026, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL
16 ADOPT REGULATIONS ESTABLISHING A RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW PROCESS FOR
17 SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITALS.
18 (2) THE REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
19 SUBSECTION SHALL:
20 (I) PROVIDE FOR A PEER–TO–PEER RECONSIDERATION OF A
21 MEDICAL NECESSITY DETERMINATION MADE BY THE DEPARTMENT OR ITS AGENT
22 ON REQUEST OF A PEDIATRIC SPECIALTY HOSPITAL;
23 (II) PROVIDE FOR RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW OF ANY MEDICAL
24 NECESSITY DETERMINATION ISSUED BY THE DEPARTMENT OR ITS AGENT DENYING:
25 1. ADMISSION TO A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL ON
26 OR AFTER JULY 1, 2025; OR
27 2. REIMBURSEMENT FOR INPATIENT SERVICES OR
28 OUTPATIENT SERVICES PROVIDED BY A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL ON OR AFTER
29 JULY 1, 2025;
30 (III) COMPLY WITH TITLE 10, SUBTITLE 2 OF THE STATE
31 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 1376
1 (IV) PROVIDE THAT THE RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW PROCESS BE
2 CONDUCTED BY A LICENSED PHYSICIAN.
3 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (2) “ADMINISTRATIVE DAY” MEANS A DAY DURING WHICH A HEALTH
6 CARE PROVIDER DELIVERS CARE TO A PATIENT WHO NO LONGER REQUIRES CARE
7 FROM THE PROVIDER BUT WHO THE PROVIDER IS UNABLE TO DISCHARGE OR
8 TRANSFER TO ANOTHER CARE SETTING.
9 (3) “MEDICALLY NECESSARY” MEANS THAT CARE IS:
10 (I) DIRECTLY RELATED TO DIAGNOSTIC, PREVENTIVE,
11 CURATIVE, PALLIATIVE, REHABILITATIVE, OR AMELIORATIVE TREATMENT OF AN
12 ILLNESS, AN INJURY, A DISABILITY, OR ANY HEALTH CONDITION;
13 (II) CONSISTENT WITH ACCEPTED STANDARDS OF GOOD
14 MEDICAL PRACTICE; AND
15 (III) NOT PRIMARILY FOR THE CONVENIENCE OF THE PATIENT,
16 THE PATIENT’S FAMILY, OR THE PROVIDER.
17 (B) The Program and the Maryland Children’s Health Program [may]:
18 (1) MAY not require prior authorization for a transfer to a special pediatric
19 hospital; BUT
20 (2) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, SHALL PROVIDE
21 A PRIOR AUTHORIZATION DETERMINATION FOR A TRANSFER TO A SPECIAL
22 PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL ON REQUEST OF THE SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR THE
23 REFERRING HEALTH CARE PROVIDER.
24 (C) IF THE PROGRAM OR MARYLAND CHILDREN’S HEALTH PROGRAM
25 RECEIVE A REQUEST UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(2) OF THIS SECTION, THE PROGRAM
26 OR MARYLAND CHILDREN’S HEALTH PROGRAM SHALL PROVIDE THE PRIOR
27 AUTHORIZATION DETERMINATION WITHIN 3 BUSINESS DAYS AFTER THE REQUEST IS
28 RECEIVED.
29 (D) (1) (I) IF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR A REFERRING
30 HEALTH CARE PROVIDER DISAGREES WITH A DETERMINATION BY THE PROGRAM OR
31 MARYLAND’S CHILDREN HEALTH PROGRAM THAT A TRANSFER TO A SPECIAL
32 PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL IS NOT MEDICALLY NECESSARY, THE SPECIAL PEDIATRIC
33 HOSPITAL OR THE REFERRING HEALTH CARE PROVIDER MAY REQUEST A

HOUSE BILL 1376 5
1 RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW BY THE PROGRAM OR MARYLAND CHILDREN’S HEALTH
2 PROGRAM IN ACCORDANCE WITH TITLE 10, SUBTITLE 2 OF THE STATE
3 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
4 (II) THE PROGRAM OR MARYLAND CHILDREN’S HEALTH
5 PROGRAM SHALL CONDUCT A REQUESTED RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW EVEN IF THE
6 ENROLLEE WILL NOT BENEFIT FINANCIALLY FROM THE OUTCOME OF THE APPEAL.
7 (2) IF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR A REFERRING HEALTH
8 CARE PROVIDER REQUESTS A RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF
9 THIS SUBSECTION, THE SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR THE REFERRING HEALTH
10 CARE PROVIDER SHALL BE REIMBURSED FOR ALL ADMINISTRATIVE DAYS AT THE
11 APPLICABLE RATE FROM THE DATE OF THE MEDICAL NECESSITY DETERMINATION
12 UNTIL THE CONCLUSION OF THE RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW.
13 Article – Insurance
14 15–861.
15 (a) (1) In this section[, “special] THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE
16 MEANINGS INDICATED.
17 (2) “ADMINISTRATIVE DAY” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 15–158
18 OF THE HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE.
19 (3) “MEDICALLY NECESSARY” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 15–158
20 OF THE HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE.
21 (4) “SPECIAL pediatric hospital” has the meaning stated in § 15–101 of
22 the Health – General Article.
23 (b) This section applies to:
24 (1) insurers and nonprofit health service plans that provide hospital,
25 medical, or surgical benefits to individuals or groups on an expense–incurred basis under
26 health insurance policies or contracts that are issued or delivered in the State; and
27 (2) health maintenance organizations that provide hospital, medical, or
28 surgical benefits to individuals or groups under contracts that are issued or delivered in
29 the State.
30 (c) An entity subject to this section:
31 (1) may not require prior authorization for a transfer to a special pediatric
32 hospital; BUT

6 HOUSE BILL 1376
1 (2) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION, SHALL PROVIDE
2 A PRIOR AUTHORIZATION DETERMINATION FOR A TRANSFER TO A SPECIAL
3 PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL ON REQUEST OF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR A
4 REFERRING HEALTH CARE PROVIDER.
5 (D) IF AN ENTITY SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION RECEIVES A REQUEST UNDER
6 SUBSECTION (C)(2) OF THIS SECTION, THE ENTITY SHALL PROVIDE THE PRIOR
7 AUTHORIZATION DETERMINATION WITHIN 3 BUSINESS DAYS AFTER THE REQUEST IS
8 RECEIVED.
9 (E) (1) IF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR A REFERRING HEALTH
10 CARE PROVIDER DISAGREES WITH A DETERMINATION BY THE ENTITY THAT A
11 TRANSFER TO A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL IS NOT MEDICALLY NECESSARY, THE
12 SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR THE REFERRING HEALTH CARE PROVIDER MAY
13 REQUEST A RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW BY THE ENTITY THAT MADE THE
14 DETERMINATION.
15 (2) THE ENTITY THAT IS REQUESTED TO CONDUCT THE
16 RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW SHALL CONDUCT THE REVIEW EVEN IF THE INSURED WILL
17 NOT BENEFIT FINANCIALLY FROM THE OUTCOME OF THE APPEAL.
18 (3) IF A SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR A REFERRING HEALTH
19 CARE PROVIDER REQUESTS A RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF
20 THIS SUBSECTION, THE SPECIAL PEDIATRIC HOSPITAL OR THE REFERRING HEALTH
21 CARE PROVIDER SHALL BE REIMBURSED FOR ALL ADMINISTRATIVE DAYS AT THE
22 APPLICABLE RATE FROM THE DATE OF THE MEDICAL NECESSITY DETERMINATION
23 UNTIL THE CONCLUSION OF THE RETROSPECTIVE REVIEW.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall apply to all
25 policies, contracts, and health benefit plans issued, delivered, or renewed in the State on or
26 after January 1, 2027.
27 SECTION 3. 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
28 January 1, 2027 July 1, 2026.

